'''Bonne Glacier''' ({{Coord|77|53|S|163|50|E|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a steep [[glacier]] {{convert|1|nmi|km|0}} west-southwest of [[Hobbs Peak]], descending northwest from [[Hobbs Ridge]] into [[Blue Glacier (Antarctica)|Blue Glacier]], in [[Victoria Land]]. The name is one of a group in the area associated with [[surveying]] applied in 1993 by the [[New Zealand Geographic Board]]. It was named after the [[Bonne projection|Bonne map projection]], a derivative [[conical projection]], in which the [[Circle of latitude|parallels]] are spaced at true distances along [[Meridian (geography)|meridians]] which are plotted as curves.<ref name=gnis/>

